.TH BART 1 "December 2025" "v0.1.0" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
bart \- directory usage analyzer and visualizer
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B bart
[\fIOPTIONS\fR] [\fIPATH\fR]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B bart
is a command-line utility that scans directories and displays a tree-like structure containing file sizes and counts. It is designed to help users visualize disk usage with colorful output and size bars.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.BR \-d ", " \-\-depth " \fIDEPTH\fR"
Specify the maximum recursion depth to display. The default is 1.
.TP
.BR \-n ", " \-\-limit " \fILIMIT\fR"
Limit the number of entries displayed per directory. Set to 0 to show all entries. The default is 0.
.TP
.BR \-s ", " \-\-sort " \fISORT\fR"
Sort the entries by \fBsize\fR or \fBname\fR. The default is \fBsize\fR.
.TP
.BR \-h ", " \-\-help
Print help information.
.TP
.BR \-V ", " \-\-version
Print version information.
.SH ARGUMENTS
.TP
.I PATH
The directory to scan. Defaults to the current directory (".").
.SH EXAMPLES
.B bart
.RS 4
Scan the current directory with default settings.
.RE
.PP
.B bart \-\-depth 2 src/
.RS 4
Scan the 'src/' directory with a depth of 2.
.RE
.PP
.B bart \-n 5 \-\-sort name
.RS 4
Show only the first 5 entries per directory, sorted by name.
.RE
.SH AUTHOR
AdminX
